name: Brad Baker
bio: Racer at heart 🏁 T6 Spinal Cord Injury ♿️ @kelceybaker6 💍 @brystalbullet 🐾💜

social_posts.post_text: It’s been 3 years today since this angel and I got engaged. Asking her to Marry me is definitely the best decision I’ve ever made. She has made me a better man in every sense of the way. I couldn’t think of a more caring, hardworking and beautiful woman to spend the rest of my life with. I love you baby! 💜
Merry Christmas everyone, from our family to yours! ❤️🌲

Reminiscing this morning of riding my dirt bike at my home track where I grew up. I sure had a lot of fun there just riding by myself seeing how fast I could go. I didn’t fully realize how lucky I was to have a nice track at my house until I moved away and didn’t have a place to ride anytime I wanted anymore. My best word of advice to any rider at any level of experience is to just ride as much as you possibly can. You should feel like you’re one with the motorcycle every time you get on it. When you’re comfortable and confident you will always perform at your best 💪🏼

Happy Valentines Day to my beautiful wife, @kelceybaker6 😘 thank you baby for being the amazing selfless woman that you are and for loving me unconditionally! 😘 We just got back from our honeymoon at 2am this morning where we stayed at @sandalsnegril in Negril, Jamaica for 5 days and 6 nights. We had such an amazing time! The weather was great, the food was great and the Jamaican people were so kind and accommodating. We made some amazing new friends; Nick and Faith from Illinois and James and Fiona from the UK. They made our trip so more fun and we all plan to keep in touch to all do something else together in the future. I love how peoples lives can connect like that! Kelcey and I even got to go parasailing thanks to Nick for packing me out to the boat and the awesome dudes on the boat for getting me all situated. It feels really good for Kelcey and i to still be able to do things like that together! Now it’s back to reality but luckily it’s 50 degrees in Michigan today so we are getting broke in before it gets really cold again 😂

I made a special surprise visit to my great friend @albertcostabalboa 😁 Albert and I met at the first Superprestegio i competed in almost a decade ago and since then we have become more like family. He is competing in the @fiawec_official at @sebringraceway about 3 hours away from Daytona. I couldn’t not stay a little longer in FL before flying home without coming to see him. You don’t have to twist my arm either to spend a day around badass race cars haha 🤪

Happy heavenly 70th birthday, dad! 🙌🏻 it’s crazy that you have already been gone 5 years now. I miss you everyday!! Looking back on photos like this remind me of just how lucky I was to have such a loving and supportive father like you. I love you dad, rest in peace! ❤️

It was great to visit with our friends at @hrc_motogp 🏁
I sure wish @marcmarquez93 was here healthy and ready to race but it’s cool to see the #6 on his bike 😜 I hope you are healed up and back to 100% soon mate 💪🏼 @stefanbradl6 put up a good fight and bring home a strong finish in the meantime 👊🏼

Just giving @alexrins some tips on how to go fast on Friday 😜 all jokes aside I’m super happy for Alex, the whole @lcr.team and @hondaracingcorporation for a much deserved and long awaited win. It was awesome to get to spend some time with my good friends @marc._.ca and @dakotamamola who got me up to speed with everything that has evolved in @motogp since the last time I was at a GP some 6 years ago. I’m amazed by the technology that has been implemented to make these already incredible machines that much better and faster. It makes me wonder if there will ever be a ceiling of how fast they can actually go 🤷🏻‍♂️ this is part of what makes @motogp so entertaining to follow and is what real racing is all about 🏁
Thank you @natelepain for taking the pic, it was nice to meet you! 👊🏼

I’m happy to announce that I will be the grand marshal for the big race at the @lodicyclebowl tomorrow evening! I was honored to be asked to do this at such a legendary race track that I first  came to back in 2000 when I was only 7 years old. I have made so many great friends there and have had many great battles on the race track. I look forward to seeing everyone who attends tomorrow night and helping some upcoming racers 🏁

Brystal turned 2 today 😀🎉 she has been doing so good, the last check up she had her kidney values had actually got better 🙌🏼 @kelceybaker6 made her a delicious kidney safe cake today which she loved and she got all sorts of treats and played plenty of ball. I never would of thought a dog could bring so much love and joy to our lives like she has 💜

location.city_name: Comunitat Valenciana Moto Gp Valencia Spain

social_posts.post_text: A cool #flashback Friday victory burnout after the inaugural Spanish Flat Track Championship in Valencia Spain. This series was put on by the great people at @noyescamp 🏁 I can’t thank them enough for bringing me over to be apart of this event, what a great memory it is now 🙌🏼 thank you @andrews_rubio @flattracklive for capturing this awesome photo 👊🏼
First bike night in the books with my babies promoting #bakersbash coming up on July 15th. Had the @brothers_powersports 450’s on display to attract some attention 🏁

I’ve been a little quiet about what my roll has been at the AFT races this year. Thanks to the kind and generous, Mike Vinson of Vinson Construction, I have had the pleasure to work with and coach 5 awesome riders this season which are; @colezabala @hunterbauer24 @tarren__santero @treyganbirdsong149 and @ksciscoe_61 🏁 They all work hard to get the results they desire but don’t forget to have a good time during the process which is the way it should be. The last race in Kentucky it was Mike’s 75th birthday which was awesome that we all got to celebrate it with him! The next race is coming up next weekend at the Du Quion Magic Mile. I’m looking forward to helping these boys put it up front 💪🏼
Happy 29th birthday to my beautiful wife, @kelceybaker6 ❤️ thank you for being the amazing woman you are and loving me unconditionally. 🙌🏼 I hope you enjoy the last year of your 20’s, I love you 😘

It’s race day at the Du Quion Magic Mile and this is definitely one of those tracks that stings to sit and watch from the sidelines. The last time we had a national here in 2015 was arguably the best time I ever had on a motorcycle. I held the legendary XR750 wide open all the way around for the majority of the day only to occasionally  let it breath a little in the middle of 3 and 4 where it was a bit slippery. I won the dash for cash and was in killer battle with @bsmith.4 @jaredmeesracing and @coolbeth2 in the main until I unfortunately had a mechanical failure with only 6 laps to go. I’m hoping I can rub some of my speed off on the riders I’m helping today so they can be battling towards the front of the pack. 💪🏼
Happy Father Day to all the great fathers out there! I am so fortunate to had/have some of the best fathers in my life a person could ask for 🙌🏼

Happy birthday to one of closest friends that’s more like a brother to me, @k_ando25 
Thank you for always being there for me and for all of the great times and memories 🏁🍻✊🏼🤙🏼 I’m looking forward to making many more in the future, love ya buddy!

#flashback Friday to my first ever GNC Twins win in Hagerstown Maryland that was exactly 10 years ago today. It’s crazy to think it’s already been that long! 🥲 We were a small team with a small budget but had a huge amount of heart and determination. Dave Atherton, who is taking the victory lap with me, would work from 5am to 3pm at United Trailers and then come home and work on my XR’s in the evening. I was a secondary mechanic on the twins and I ran my own singles program. I remember dropping Dave and Vikki off at the AFT credential trailer to get their pit passes that day cause we didn’t have enough money at the beginning of the year to just buy them season credentials. By the time they got their pit passes and made it down to the pits I had already unloaded my 95 Econoline and had the pit area completely set up. Times have definitely changed since then but I’m proud to say I won my first national and the Grand National Championship in this fashion that year. It’s part of what has shaped who I am today and has given me so much knowledge that I’m ready to share with the riders I’m helping here in New York tomorrow. 🏁

Happy 2nd year anniversary to my beautiful, loving, caring and selfless wife, @kelceybaker6 ❤️ crazy it’s already been 2 years! We unfortunately didn’t get to celebrate today cause we were still busy wrapping things up after a busy race weekend but we will definitely have to make up for it soon! Thank you for always being by my side, I love you baby 😘

The second annual @bulletstrongracing Baker’s Bash is done and dusted. What a crazy long and busy week it was but also a very fun one! Mother Nature sure had us stressed out all week dumping several inches of rain some nights and the forecast constantly changing day to day. When I woke up on Saturday morning and it was raining i almost thought for sure we’d have to cancel because the track already had some extremely wet and soft spots the night before. But thankfully the rains subsiding and especially thanks to my track crew we were able to get it in. It definitely takes a small village of great people to pull one of these races off successfully and we thankfully have an amazing team!

Thank you to all the riders, families, and the fans for coming out to support our event. We hope you had a great time! We will making notes to clean things up to make things better for next year. 
We hope to see you all there again! 🏁

July 22nd, 5 years ago is the day my life changed forever. Even though it may have changed, it didn’t end. I’m still here trying to live life the best I can. I have so many great people in my life that make staying positive a lot easier and for them I’m super thankful. Please watch the video to find out a little of what I have been doing and where my recovery is at.

In honor of the Peoria TT tomorrow let’s rewind 10 years to when I wrapped up the expert singles championship at the legendary race track. I won the dash for cash and came in a 2nd in the main that day. The track was prepared awesome so it was a blast to ride! Tomorrow I’ll be playing role as team owner/crew chief but I’m just as eager to put in a good result! 💪🏼

As most of you know, the @americanflattrack #peoriatt didn’t exactly end the way that we had hoped. Coming into the day we knew we were going to be the underdogs since Ferran has only ridden flat track a handful of times this year because he has been committed to racing the Spanish and French supermoto championship and this would be his first time riding a brand new motorcycle we just had just put together. He started out the day staying inside the top 10 in qualifying and each time he went out on the track he got more comfortable with the bike and the track. In his heat race he finished 4th right behind the leaders securing him a second row start for the main event. In the main he got a great start, which is unlike him haha, and finished the first lap in 5th. But then on lap 2 he had a big ohhh s$!t moment coming off turn 2 when he hit a slick spot that snapped the bike sideways and I thought for sure he was going over the high side but somehow he managed to save it but it made him fall back to 8th. Then unfortunately, on the start of lap 10 while battling for 6th he got tangled up with another rider which resulted in him loosing the front end. As he was falling he tried to catch himself with his left hand which ultimately would dislocate his wrist from the impact 😞 we obviously weren’t happy with the situation but these things unfortunately happen in racing and we have no control over that. Ferran arrived back in Barcelona today and went straight to see his doctor to get an MRI to see if it will need surgery. Hopefully he can make a fairly quick recovery so his hopes for a championship in at least the Spanish Supermoto championship isn’t out of the cards. 🙏🏻

All in all we are proud of our performance since both the level of the competition and the equipment in this class is super high. For Ferran to show up mid season and battle with top 8 best riders and for us to have a competitive bike says a lot. I’d like to give a huge thank you to all of supporters that have stuck behind us! Without all you, there is no way we could keep the dream alive. 🏁

I had a great week in my home state visiting friends and family between Rapid City and Castle Rock. We had plenty of smiles, laughs and shared memories. Riding a motorcycle is a lot fun but the relationships we build with our friends and family at the track is what keeps us coming back year after year. ❤️🏁

I had a great time in Tulsa Oklahoma this weekend hanging out and helping the @xtreemflattrack crew. It’s always fun to get back to some grass roots type of racing and to meet and talk to new people. The kids standing in this photo rode hard and put on a good show all weekend. I have to give a huge thanks to the man standing on the right of this photo, Mike Vinson of Vinson Construction. If it wasn’t for him, myself and at least 6 other racers wouldn’t of been at the race track this year. It’s generous and kind guys like him that are the glue that keeps our sport together.

I had a good time signing autographs with these 3 legends today; Jay Springsteen, Scotty Parker and @bsmith.4 
Thanks @raycshd for having us!

In honor of September being Spinal Cord Injury awareness month I’ve created a team fundraiser through @wingsforlife to help raise funds for the cause. I’m super thankful for programs like @wingsforlife that privately raise money and spread awareness to help fund research to find a cure for spinal cord injuries, because without them, people like myself wouldn’t have hope. I would greatly appreciate you all if you would donate anything you can afford to help me reach my fundraising goal. 🙏🏻 You can find the link to donate in my bio at the top of my page. Thank you and god bless!

I finally got to return all the favors Doctor Henry Small has done for me by building him this badass Maddog bike to ride at @colin_edwards_ttbc 
For those of you that don’t know who Doc Henry is, he is the great doctor that fixed my extremely broken elbow after I broke it when a student rider fell down in front me almost 10 years ago at the Bootcamp. Since then, he has helped me recover from every one of my injuries. He has helped many top riders recover the best they can and get back on track as soon as possible after the worst happens. He has rode and raced motorcycles his whole life and is a regular at the Bootcamp tearing it up on maddog bikes. He reached out to me a few years ago to ask if I would be interested in building him a weapon for the Bootcamp and I was happy and excited to take on the project. What I chose to do is put a pissed off XR 100 engine in a 1998 CR 80 chassis.

I have to give a huge shout out to all the people that helped me with the build; Mike Velasco for building a killer engine @savagecustomfabrication for building a custom aluminum gas tank, starter drive, intake, oil cooler, foot pegs and many other things, @prowheelracing for the sweet wheels, @motionpro for the controls, @fusiongraphix for the sweet graphics, @saddlemen for the seat over, @odigrips for the bars,  grips and billet bar ends @brothers_powersports for the Honda parts, nickel plated hardware by @specbolt - @mikametals for the chain and sprockets @kfgperformance for the suspension work @2wdw for the help with tuning @seventeenmotorsports for doing a lot of the labor, my brother @scotteb11 for helping with the labor, @kenanduncan for coating parts and last but not least one of my best buds @jacoblehmann4 for helping me put the finishing touches on the the project and deliver it to the Bootcamp this past weekend.
.
Unfortunately, Doc Henry had an emergency to attend to so he couldn’t be there to ride it but I was able to take it for a spin up and down the road to see how she runs! 😜 it felt good to ride a bike again and I can at least say I rode it once.

#throwbackthursday to this past weekend when my beautiful wife @kelceybaker6 and I visited Nashville for the first time to meet up with our friends that we met in Jamaica earlier this year while we were on our honeymoon. This awesome city definitely doesn’t disappoint and having great company like we did made it that much more fun. 👌🏼🇺🇸🤙🏼

#throwbackthursday to this summers Peoria TT bike build with my amigo @juansantiagorodriguez37 

First off, I’d like to give a huge thank you to the @brothers_powersports for supplying us with a brand new 2023 Honda CRF 450. The Brothers has been behind me since I was 12 years old and are like family to me now. They have a wide selection of dirt bikes, street bikes, ATV’s, UTV’s, Jet Ski’s, Snowmobiles, Timbersleds and trailers. If you’re located in the the Pacific NW, check them out if you’re in the market.

Secondly, I have to give a huge thanks to my father in law, Mike Stauffer, for building us a rocket ship of an engine. I’ve been very fortunate to have been able to work around some amazing engine builders in my career and Mike is one of, if not thee best I’ve had to pleasure to learn from.

I’d also like to give a huge thank you to one of my great friends, Jimmy Wood, from @ohlinsusa for supplying us with some awesome suspension.
Jimmy has been able to take his experience and knowledge from previously being a rider that could contend with and beat the best riders in the sport and apply it to working with riders to develop some amazing  suspension settings. When he teamed up with Ohlins and started using their state of the art components it took his suspension to the next level.

Other supporters include; @motionpro for quality controls and tools, @odigrips for top shelf grips and handlebars, @fusiongraphix for the sweet graphics, @rekluse_motorsports & @pz5cobra for the trick clutch set up, @evanspowersport for the waterless coolant, @mikametals for the quality chain, @flyracingusa for the stand and parts, @saddlemen for the seat and bike cover, @webcamshafts for the custom camshaft, @gennkoracing for the sprockets, @galfermoto & @pz5cobra for the sweet brake set up, @specbolt for the quality hardware, @hammerheaddesigns  for the brake and shift levers

Last but not least I’d like to thank Jerry from @roofsystemsdfw along with @vinson52748 from Vinson Construction as well as Ryan from @vanillacycles, Eric from @1stimpressions_raceteam and Dick Ford for helping fund it all. 👊🏼

I was very fortunate to harvest this dandy of a buck yesterday evening. It’s definitely a different feeling and a rush when a big guy like this steps out of the woods haha. Huge thanks to my great friend, Dan Shaw and his family for letting me hunt on their land and field dressing the deer for me afterwords! For those wondering about my “blind” i have a permit to be able to hunt from my car since I’m disabled. I’ll take the perks where I can get them lol. This guy is going to taste good on the dinner table and look good on the wall in my man cave 😋😎

#flashbackfriday to one of my last times racing the legendary XR 750 at Willow Springs in 2016. These races at Willow put on by Eddie and Jody Mulder were so much fun!! The track was always prepped to the 9’s and there was a bunch of cash on the line to win. I forget how much money I won in this dash for cash but it was a lot, partially why I was so stoked when I crossed the finish lol. The @dodge_bros_racing XR was definitely hooked up and running good that day. God, I sure love that sound haha. Big thanks to @schmiriam.deitcher with @flattracklive for capturing all these awesome races over the years so we can always look back on these memories.
Merry Christmas from our family to yours! I hope you all have had an amazing day ❤️🌲🎁

#throwbackthursday to attending the #daytona200 memorial on Daytona Beach back in 2014. I had the honor to be able to visit with and hear some awesome old race stories from some true legends, like this guy, the late Bobby Hill. Bobby was one of the original @indianmotorcycle #wreckingcrew members back in the 50’s where he won the grand national championship in 51 and 52.. Who would have thought that three years later I would be apart of the new Indian wrecking crew to help carry on the legacy. I’m sure grateful for all the cool moments like this I was able to be apart of during my career. Race in peace original wrecking crew; Bobby Hill, Bill Tuman and Earnie Beckman 🙏🏻🏁

The world has unfortunately lost a great man, a legend, my dear friend, Mike Velasco. Mike has been one of my biggest supporters ever since I was only 12 years old when he started building my brother and I’s race engines. I’ll always remember showing up to @brothers_powersports for the first time to meet him and have him show us around. He made us feel right at home, like we were apart of the family from the very beginning. He was always so positive and happy, it was like nothing ever phased him, no matter how many difficult projects he had in front of him. He had a way of always putting a smile on my face, especially when he would let out his infectious laugh when talking about some of the crazy things he would do to make horsepower back in the early days of Superbikes. I owe so much to him, he contributed to so much to my success. Every engine he ever built for me was fast, I hardly ever had a mechanical and he never ever charged me a dime. I’ll admit, back then I feel like I took him for granted. I wish i could go back and do more for him to let him know just how much i appreciated him. But I mainly need to thank him for just being a great friend. After my accident he would always check in on me to see how I was doing and he never stopped helping me even though I wasn’t racing anymore and he was retired. I’m really glad that he was able to be apart of building the supermini that I just recently finished. We had a lot of fun talking back and forth during that project. I’ll always cherish the memories we had together. Mike will deeply missed by the many people he helped and touched over the years and he will definitely never be forgotten. My heart and thoughts go out to his awesome family during this very difficult time. Race in Peace Mike, see you on the other side my friend 🙏🏻❤️🏁

It’s crazy to think it’s already been a decade since the first @superprestigio_dtx .
To tell you the truth, I really didn’t know just how significant the event was back then. I was just a 20 year old kid enjoying the moment. But looking back on it now, i realize how lucky I was to have that experience. I’m happy to say that I established friendships with people during that trip that are like family to me now. I guess that goes to show that what I did off the track was more important than what I did on the track. I hope to make a trip back to Spain this year to visit everyone, it’s been way too long!
Racer at heart 🏁 T6 Spinal Cord Injury ♿️ @kelceybaker6 💍 @brystalbullet 🐾💜
